Coordonate system for Java 2D and used Topology:

 0
0*------------------------------------>
 |		N
 |		
 |		|
 |		|
 |		|
 |    W --------*-------- E
 |		|
 |		|
 |		|
 |		
 |		S
 |
 Y

* boulder.adt describes the abstract data-type
*  adt-to-tom -n boulder --nojar --input boulder.adt --javagen --package boulderdash 

* tom BoulderDashCore.t
* javac *.java
* java BoulderDash2D or appletviewer BoulderDash2d.java

To run the applet needs to find classes for shared-objects, jjTraveler and ATerm-java... 
The jar file "boulder.jar" shall be used, see BoulderDashNTom.html.

To run boulderdash as a java application under eclipse, take care to set 
the working directory to ${workspace_loc:jtom/examples} in the "Arguments" tab of the "run" window

